# CrowdGuard environment configuration
#
# Every variable below is OPTIONAL. With none set, the web app still runs:
# the dashboards render built-in sample data, and the RAG assistant uses
# offline keyword search. Set a variable to switch that capability to live data.
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in only what you need.

# --- Supabase (database) ---------------------------------------------------
# When BOTH are set, the database-backed API routes (incidents, anomalies,
# lost-persons, crowd-density, ...) read/write your Supabase project. When
# absent, those routes return empty data (the dashboards show sample data).
# Schema + seed: scripts/01-create-tables.sql and scripts/02-seed-data.sql
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# --- Google Generative AI (Gemini) -----------------------------------------
# Enables Gemini `text-embedding-004` for the RAG knowledge base used by the
# emergency-protocol assistant (/api/chat). When absent, the assistant falls
# back to offline keyword search. GEMINI_API_KEY is accepted as an alias.
GOOGLE_API_KEY=

# --- Python ML backend ------------------------------------------------------
# Not configured here: the web app calls the FastAPI ML service at the
# hardcoded URL http://localhost:8001 (see ml-backend/). Start it to enable
# live crowd forecasting (XGBoost) and CCTV anomaly detection (YOLOv8).
